## Install Python (Requires SUDO)

```shell
ansible-playbook -vvv main.yml -i "localhost" --connection="localhost" --extra-vars "state=present" -t="python" -K
```

## Uninstall Python venv support only (Requires SUDO)

```shell
ansible-playbook -vvv main.yml -i "localhost" --connection="localhost" --extra-vars "state=absent" -t="python" -K
```

This intentionally removes only the `python3-venv` package. The base `python3` interpreter is left installed because removing the system Python package on Ubuntu can break core package dependencies.